HEADWORD: Wanness
<hw>Wan"ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state
of being wan; a sallow, dead, pale color; paleness; pallor; <as>as, the
<ex>wanness</ex> of the cheeks after a fever</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

